# === Windows reserved-name junk (PowerShell redirection pollution) — DO NOT REMOVE ===
# These names cannot exist as files on Windows (they are device names), but a
# broken `Out-File NUL` / `> NUL` redirection can create a real file that
# fs.unlinkSync cannot delete. A NUL inside .homeybuild hangs tar-stream and
# produces a 0-byte / corrupt archive = root cause of Athom "processing_failed".
# Excluding them here is a last-resort guard if one slips back in.
NUL
CON
PRN
AUX
COM1
COM2
COM3
COM4
COM5
COM6
COM7
COM8
COM9
LPT1
LPT2
LPT3
LPT4
LPT5
LPT6
LPT7
LPT8
LPT9

